UKCP psychotherapist Alivia Rose @LivvyChrissie talks to
@edcumming for @thetimes. 

Alivia unpacks the strain parenting during the pandemic has put on relationships. Read it here: https://t.co/4T6fyKYQ6G #Parenting #Pandemic #Covid19

So many aspects of our lives have changed over the last year #Covid19. 

Big change can trigger a cycle of emotions that can be difficult to navigate. In our latest podcast we seek advice from UKCP psychotherapist Alivia Rose 
@LivvyChrissie: https://t.co/uzphE12QB2 #Podcast

As we approach sunnier days it's important that we find time to de-stress, especially after such a difficult year #Covid19. 

Listen to our podcast with UKCP member  Susan Smith  
@TheStresshacker this #StessAwarenessMonth and uncover how to switch off: https://t.co/K6qtVdlZzo

From lawyer to psychotherapist, UKCP member John-Paul Davies 
@Trusted_Place tells us about his journey into the profession. 

Read it here: https://t.co/WZ6hLIvLkO #Training #Psychotherapy

Relocating our lives can be so much more complicated than we first think, especially when the decision affects our children. 

UKCP psychotherapist Dr @AlfredoGozho speaks to 
@guardian journalist @AnnalisaB to offer advice. Read it here: https://t.co/jnUBhUwhjS #Moving #Family

'Many people fear that without self-doubt, they may become arrogant', UKCP psychotherapist Neil Turner 
@tweets4therapy told @happifulhq @ellenlorna. 

But how can we overcome our own inner critic? Read it here: https://t.co/xBc1GqYx7b #SelfDoubt #FridayReads

